For YSSY (Sydney Airport):
- Aerodrome control tower is operating at reduced capacity due to operational restrictions, which may affect helicopter operations.
- There have been changes to the standard instrument departure procedures. The Deena Seven (Jet) RNAV SID for Runway 16R has been deleted and replaced with the Kampl Six (RNAV) SID.
- There have been changes to the declared distances. The approach gradient for Runway 07 is now 3.3 percent and there are changes to the takeoff distances for various runways.
- The Instrument Landing System (ILS) for Runway 07 is unserviceable.
- Runway 07/25 is closed due to work in progress.
- Certain taxiways are limited to use due to work in progress.
- The taxiway centerline lights on TWY B1 are unserviceable.
- There have been changes to the declared distances. The approach gradient for Runway 16L is now 3.8 percent and for Runway 16R is 2.7 percent due to obstacles.
- An obstacle crane has been erected at a distance of 3.24NM from the airport.
- The taxiway centerline lights at one of the intermediate holding points on TWY A are unserviceable.
- There have been changes to the aerodrome and approach lighting, with the high intensity runway lights being LED type.
- There will be a fireworks display at Carss Point, located at a bearing of 213 degrees from the airport.

There are no specific notams relevant to the user's question. The closest match is the closure of Runway 07/25 due to work in progress.

Considering the greater circle distance, the user may want to consider the notams for the airports in the vicinity of YMAY (Albury Airport), YMES (Essendon Airport), YSCB (Canberra Airport), and YSWG (Wagga Wagga Airport).
